[26.057016, "o", "# Handoff Brief — `(no branch)`\r\n\r\n| Field      | Value |\r\n|------------|-------|\r\n| From       | claude-code ×4 (4 sessions, 762 turns) |\r\n| To         | claude-code |\r\n| Generated  | 2026-04-25 07:03 UTC |\r\n| Branch dif | +1863 / -19 across 26 files |\r\n\r\n## What I'm working on\r\n\r\nTwo parallel workstreams on the Drift AI project: (1) migrating the `drift_ai` repository from the `shellfans-dev` GitHub account to `ShellFans-Kirin` via a seven-phase plan (M1–M7), and (2) developing the v0.1.1 patch release focused on Anthropic API integration. The migration is paused mid-M2 awaiting the user to manually accept the GitHub transfer invitation in the web UI, after PAT scope and target-namespace blockers were resolved. The v0.1.1 work has completed Phase 0 environment verification and entered Phase A (Anthropic integration scoping: streaming, error classification, context window handling, token logging, retries) with no production code committed yet. Several edits to core files (capture.rs, main.rs, Cargo.toml, drift.rb.template) were rejected during the last session and need to be reattempted or rethought.\r\n\r\n## Progress so far\r\n\r\n- ✅ M1 pre-flight checks: PAT validation, target repo verification, release metadata capture\r\n- ⏳ M2 repo transfer — invitation sent, awaiting manual user acceptance in GitHub web UI\r\n- ⏳ v0.1.1 Phase A: Anthropic API integration scoping and secure token setup\r\n- ⏸ M3–M7 migration phases (git remote updates, CI secrets, homebrew tap, docs, announcement)\r\n- ⏸ v0.1.1 production code for streaming, retries, token logging in drift-core/compaction.rs\r\n\r\n## Files in scope\r\n\r\n### `drift_ai/crates/drift-core/src/compaction.rs` (created, +1195 / -12)\r\n\r\n```\r\n(could not read working-tree file at drift_ai/crates/drift-core/src/compaction.rs)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### `drift_ai/docs/ACCOUNT-MIGRATION-REPORT.md` (created, +150 / -0)\r\n"]
